{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/74860", "id": 457527055, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDU3NTI3MDU1", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/74860", "diff_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/74860.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/74860.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/74860", "number": 74860, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "[android] Add support for android's file descriptor ownership tagging to libstd.", "user": {"login": "jmgao", "id": 593995, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjU5Mzk5NQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/593995?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jmgao", "html_url": "https://github.com/jmgao", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jmgao/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jmgao/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jmgao/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jmgao/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jmgao/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jmgao/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jmgao/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jmgao/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jmgao/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "Android has started investigating using Rust for system components, and one of the biggest historical sources of bugs we've had in cross-language interop has been caused by confusion around file descriptor ownership, since you're forced to pass file descriptors across language boundaries as a bare int without any type information about whether ownership is being transferred. The bugs this results in are horrible to debug, because they're nondeterministic and manifest as impossible behavior occurring on different threads. (e.g. [[1](https://www.sqlite.org/howtocorrupt.html#_continuing_to_use_a_file_descriptor_after_it_has_been_closed)], [[2](https://engineering.fb.com/ios/debugging-file-corruption-on-ios/)])\r\n\r\nWe've added [some facilities to our libc](https://android.googlesource.com/platform/bionic/+/refs/heads/master/libc/include/android/fdsan.h) to detect/prevent this class of bugs. Basically, user code can tell libc that a file descriptor can only be closed with a specified token, and to abort/log an error if someone tries to close the fd without the token (the behavior is process-wide and configurable at runtime, but the default on Android R (API level 30) and beyond is to abort). We've found dozens of bugs in Android with this, and hopefully prevented many more from ever being checked in.\r\n\r\nThis PR makes libstd use this on android when available. It potentially changes behavior, but only for code that's either broken, or very weird (e.g. `File::from_raw_fd(fd).into_raw_fd()` sequences which construct a File that owns the fd, and then removes it from the File before drop), and also only for unsafe code, I believe.\r\n\r\n~(also, as another commit in this PR, I improved the error handling on non-android close. Let me know if I should split this out to a separate PR)~ (whoops, didn't actually build this commit: I'll do this as a followup)", "created_at": "2020-07-28T04:01:37Z", "updated_at": "2022-03-15T14:54:42Z", "closed_at": "2021-01-15T13:06:11Z", "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "28952bee990aef9f92122346b1129f79c30cefab", "assignee": {"login": "nikomatsakis", "id": 155238, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE1NTIzOA==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/155238?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis", "html_url": "https://github.com/nikomatsakis", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.